 of SpO2SpO2 is a measure of the amount of oxygen-carrying hemoglobin in the blood relative to the amount of hemoglobin not carrying oxygen and is an important parameter of the human respiratory cycle.
The device SpO2 reference values are as follows, with lower values indicating a higher risk: 
Daily activities: generally ≥ 95%
Nocturnal sleep: generally ≥ 90%
